ANATOMICAL MARKET FRAMEWORK (AMF) v1.0
======================================
Author: Sadisha
Date:   March 2026


OVERVIEW
--------
The Anatomical Market Framework (AMF) is an analytical structure for
dissecting and understanding markets by mapping their core components to
biological analogues. Just as anatomy reveals how a living system is
organised and functions, AMF reveals how a market is structured,
circulates value, and sustains itself.


CORE COMPONENTS
---------------

1. SKELETON — Market Infrastructure
   The underlying structures that give the market its shape and stability:
   exchanges, clearing houses, regulatory bodies, and settlement systems.

2. CIRCULATORY SYSTEM — Capital Flow
   The mechanisms by which value moves through the market: credit channels,
   liquidity facilities, payment rails, and investment pipelines.

3. NERVOUS SYSTEM — Information & Signals
   Price discovery, data feeds, analyst research, regulatory disclosures,
   and any signal that coordinates participant behaviour.

4. MUSCULATURE — Active Participants
   The agents that drive market movement: market makers, institutional
   investors, retail traders, arbitrageurs, and algorithmic systems.

5. ORGANS — Functional Subsystems
   Specialised market segments (e.g. primary vs secondary markets, spot vs
   derivatives) that perform distinct but interdependent functions.

6. IMMUNE SYSTEM — Risk Management & Regulation
   Circuit breakers, margin requirements, stress-testing regimes, and
   regulatory oversight that defend market integrity against systemic shocks.

7. METABOLISM — Value Creation & Destruction
   The rate at which capital is deployed, returned, written off, or
   recycled — the market's throughput and efficiency.


ANALYTICAL METHOD
-----------------
To apply AMF to a given market:

  Step 1  Define the market boundary (asset class, geography, timeframe).
  Step 2  Map each anatomical component to its concrete market counterpart.
  Step 3  Identify dependencies and feedback loops between components.
  Step 4  Diagnose structural weaknesses or dysfunction (analogous to
          pathology in biological systems).
  Step 5  Derive actionable insights or intervention points.


